news.title: Pune: Kharadi residents to receive digital property cards by September 2025
news.para: The project, part of Central govt's ownership scheme launched in 2019, aims to streamline urban land management. In Pune district, it will be first implemented in Kharadi — now under the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) limits.

news.title: Jaipur: Tenants in Walled City’s crumbling buildings worry
news.para: When asked about this year's preparations, Pushpendra Singh Rathore, deputy commissioner of JMC-H's vigilance wing, said, "We have directed all zonal DCs to reassess and prepare a fresh list of structurally unsafe buildings."

news.title: Mumbai: BMC plan to auction prime plots stalled as two government bodies want to procure them
news.para: The move had marked the first time the civic body opted to auction its own plots, indicating a shift in its strategy to monetise real estate assets and generate long-term revenue. However, the auction process faced multiple hurdles.

news.title: HC junks Greater Noida development body order to cancel land for project
news.para: The court struck down restoration charges, time extension penalties, and penal interest imposed by GNIDA, asking the Authority to restore the plot and revalidate the project map.

news.title: New bylaws not enough to regularise hotels in residential areas in Rajasthan
news.para: The industry stated that while complying with rules of not hosting weddings and running rooftop restaurants catering to the general public is easy, the 60-foot road width criterion will create a hurdle for most hotels built decades ago in the vicinity of railways, monuments, and bus stands.

news.title: Not just land, now 7/12 documents for building floors too in Maharashtra
news.para: Bawankule said, "In Maharashtra, we do not have system of issuing 7/12 for vertical buildings. We will soon launch the Vertical 7/12 Yojna in state, so that residents on each of the floors will also get that document."

news.title: Build PMAY schemes with 1,000 flats in each of six constituencies: Maharashtra CM
news.para: CM Fadnavis congratulated the new homeowners and praised the quality of construction undertaken by NMC. "The same quality flat is being sold for Rs18 lakh in the adjacent scheme, but citizens are getting the flat under PMAY for Rs9 lakh," said Fadnavis.

news.title: Residents of Noida’s Amrapali Riverview society protest lack of amenities
news.para: "We held a protest march against NBCC and the CR office today from River View Society to the main gate of Gaur Project (Laser Park, Phase-3), in which a large number of men, women, elderly, and children participated" said Mritunjay Sharma from River View Society, Greater Noida West.

news.title: New policy may allow owners of old flats bigger homes for free in Noida
news.para: The policy, approved on June 14, offers existing homeowners larger apartments with a minimum 15% increase in carpet area along with temporary accommodation for the period when reconstruction will take place.

news.title: Draft housing rules in Maharashtra allow virtual AGMs, ease norms
news.para: ​​In a push toward digital inclusion, the draft allows virtual participation in annual general meetings (AGMs). Still, a quorum of two-thirds or 20 members, whichever is less, remains mandatory. If a meeting is adjourned due to lack of quorum, it can be reconvened within 7 to 30 days without requiring a quorum.

news.title: Interest on refund is like compensation in consumer disputes: NCDRC
news.para: The state commission had found the builder's service deficient and directed a refund of Rs 34,27,747 with 12% interest, Rs 1 lakh as compensation, and Rs 11,000 as litigation costs to the complainant.

news.title: Karnataka: 10 builders yet to pay ₹347 crore in penalties
news.para: When RERA was introduced, there was optimism that victims of real estate fraud would receive swift relief. However, that promise has remained largely unfulfilled.

news.title: Hong Kong's New World Development 'actively engaged' with creditors on loan refinance
news.para: The update follows media reports that the Hong Kong property developer, which has one of the highest debt ratios among its peers, is nearing a loan refinancing deal.

news.title: Maharashtra government clears four town planning schemes proposed by PMRDA
news.para: The Manjari Khurd-Kolwadi scheme was rejected on technical grounds, particularly in plot demarcation, for which the proposal will have to be re-submitted after making the appropriate changes, a PMRDA official said.

news.title: GIDA to begin plot allotment in Dhuriyapar Industrial Township
news.para: Once completed, the Dhuriyapar Industrial Township is expected to become the largest industrial land bank in Purvanchal, creating new opportunities for investors and entrepreneurs and further boosting the region's economic potential.

news.title: Gurugram civic body's panel to oversee digital land records
news.para: The panel will ensure precise updates and maintenance of municipal land documentation on the portal, and will also supervise and assess municipal land utilisation.

news.title: Raymond Realty to launch ₹14,000-crore worth housing projects in FY26
news.para: Raymond Realty CEO Harmohan Sahni announced that the company will get listed on stock exchanges on July 1, post demerger of the real estate vertical from Raymond Ltd, which will now focus on just the engineering vertical.

news.title: Goa: Court order seeking FIR in EDC land fraud matter stayed
news.para: According to the counsel, there was no reason given by the trial court for arriving at the conclusion that the FIR needs to be registered within 24 hours in accordance with the complaint.

news.title: NMMC announces 501 dangerous buildings in Navi Mumbai
news.para: These structures have been officially classified as hazardous under Section 264 of the Maharashtra Municipal Corporation Act. However, the number of such structures has reduced from last year's data of 527 which is attributed to ongoing redevelopment work of unsafe buildings.

news.title: Plan to allot houses on priority to urban poor lodged in transit houses in Bhubaneswar
news.para: A high-level meeting of the housing and urban development department was convened recently, where the decision was taken to ensure allotment of houses on a priority basis for beneficiaries staying in transit houses.
